When generating the html documentation I had lots of warning with `ln` command trying to create an already existing link.
Using `-f`option (--force) silent them.
title: DOC: fix cache symlinks warnings when generating doc.

I had an oral agreement from @AlexandreAbraham for merging this one once CI are green.
Everything is green => Merging !
AFAIR this is a kludge to share nilearn_cache from different examples folders on CircleCI, the simpler the better ...
Maybe testing if the link exist is more clever? This would let open the possibility to customize these links. This is just an open question, this is not something that I do.
